WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.671
Are you a fan
of poetry?

00:03.704 --> 00:07.808
What do you say to an evening
of "raging against
the dying of the light"?

00:13.013 --> 00:15.649
ANNOUNCER:
FX presents Better Things.

00:21.555 --> 00:23.557
(dog barking in distance)

00:31.632 --> 00:35.002
Uh, this one is
a haiku and a half.

00:35.035 --> 00:38.005
"As I counted the bracelets

00:38.038 --> 00:40.641
"on my dying mother's wrist,

00:40.674 --> 00:43.811
"it was as if
I was counting...

00:47.681 --> 00:49.683
...her pain."

00:52.086 --> 00:55.756
(scattered applause)

00:55.789 --> 00:57.525
Thank you.

00:57.558 --> 00:59.160
Thank you.

00:59.193 --> 01:01.061
WOMAN:
Congratulations, Joy.

01:01.095 --> 01:02.630
Oh...
(women whooping)

01:02.663 --> 01:04.665
Thank you,
thank you.

01:04.698 --> 01:06.667
Oh, that was really intense.

01:06.700 --> 01:09.237
(sighs)

01:09.270 --> 01:11.572
How do you know Joy?

01:11.605 --> 01:13.841
Oh, uh, college.

01:13.874 --> 01:15.576
Cool.

01:15.609 --> 01:17.111
I don't really know her.

01:17.145 --> 01:20.681
I-I just got an e-mail
saying she needed some support.

01:20.714 --> 01:22.082
Cool.

01:22.116 --> 01:25.085
ROBIN:
You have any kids?

01:25.119 --> 01:27.255
SAM:
Oh, I have three daughters.

01:27.288 --> 01:29.190
ROBIN:
You're married?

01:29.223 --> 01:31.259
SAM:
Divorced.

01:31.292 --> 01:33.861
Me, too.

01:33.894 --> 01:35.896
You have kids?

01:35.929 --> 01:39.167
I have a daughter, yeah.

01:39.200 --> 01:42.336
And how often
do you see her?

01:42.370 --> 01:43.904
Every day.

01:43.937 --> 01:46.707
How does that work?

01:46.740 --> 01:49.143
Well, I-I'm raising her.

01:49.177 --> 01:50.744
Oh.

01:50.778 --> 01:52.446
Her mom died?

01:52.480 --> 01:53.614
(chuckles):
No. No.

01:53.647 --> 01:55.082
She's-she's very much alive.

01:55.115 --> 01:56.784
After our divorce,

01:56.817 --> 01:58.752
I moved to a house
about a half a mile away,

01:58.786 --> 02:00.288
as close as I could get
to our house,

02:00.321 --> 02:01.822
so that I could be
near our daughter,

02:01.855 --> 02:03.357
but then her mom
met somebody

02:03.391 --> 02:04.792
and they moved very far away,

02:04.825 --> 02:07.461
and she has
a whole other life now.

02:07.495 --> 02:10.431
And she decided...

02:10.464 --> 02:14.402
not to raise my daughter,
so I'm doing it on my own.

02:14.435 --> 02:17.238
And how's that going?

02:17.271 --> 02:18.439
Pretty bad.

02:18.472 --> 02:19.440
(chuckles)

02:19.473 --> 02:22.042
Like your life, I guess.
Subtract two.

02:24.645 --> 02:26.146
Nice.

02:26.180 --> 02:28.148
("Everything Is New"
by Briana Marela playing)

02:28.182 --> 02:29.983
(singers vocalizing
ethereal music)

02:30.017 --> 02:32.286
*

02:49.803 --> 02:52.673
*

02:54.842 --> 02:55.809
(door opens)

02:55.843 --> 02:57.177
Mom, did you or did you not say

02:57.211 --> 02:59.480
that I could have the
minivan when I turn 16?

02:59.513 --> 03:00.781
Mom? Hi, Mommy.

03:00.814 --> 03:02.115
Can we spend time
together today?

03:02.149 --> 03:04.552
Mom, no fair.
What are you gonna do?

03:04.585 --> 03:06.086
My God, Frankie,
stop pretending like

03:06.119 --> 03:07.688
everything is a conspiracy
against you.

03:07.721 --> 03:10.524
FRANKIE: I don't want
the minivan anyway.

03:10.558 --> 03:13.761
I want a blue Mercedes,
where all the windows go down.

03:13.794 --> 03:15.963
Like, open windows.
I think it's so cute.

03:15.996 --> 03:19.066
MAX: Oh, and you think she's
just gonna buy one for you?

03:19.099 --> 03:20.834
FRANKIE: No, but, I mean,
like, if she wants one,

03:20.868 --> 03:23.837
then I could
also drive it.
MAX: Don't you like him?

03:23.871 --> 03:25.806
* What matters...
FRANKIE:
Ew, no. He's my teacher.

03:25.839 --> 03:28.208
MAX: He's a student teacher.
He's hot.

03:28.242 --> 03:32.079
* When everything
(girls continue chattering)

03:32.112 --> 03:35.283
* Is new

03:35.316 --> 03:36.717
MAX:
He has an eclectic style...

03:36.750 --> 03:38.852
(singers vocalizing)

03:38.886 --> 03:41.822
MAX:
He's quirky. I like it.

03:41.855 --> 03:43.156
FRANKIE:
That's so weird, Max.

03:43.190 --> 03:44.658
MAX: Well, who do you
have a crush on?

03:44.692 --> 03:46.126
You have a crush
on the weirdest people.

03:46.159 --> 03:48.095
FRANKIE: Excuse you?
MAX: Excuse me.

03:48.128 --> 03:49.830
FRANKIE: Like, you have a crush
on my teacher.

03:49.863 --> 03:51.399
-That's nasty.
-Your student teacher.

03:51.432 --> 03:52.900
* Be true...

03:52.933 --> 03:54.167
FRANKIE:
You think with your vagina.

03:54.201 --> 03:56.337
MAX:
That's right, I do.

03:56.370 --> 03:58.238
FRANKIE:
Yeah, and it's unfortunate,
because your vagina is stupid.

03:58.272 --> 03:59.907
It may be the only
part of your body

03:59.940 --> 04:01.174
that's dumber
than your brain.

04:01.208 --> 04:03.176
MAX: Okay, like
your vagina is a genius.

04:03.210 --> 04:04.745
FRANKIE: My vagina
is going to invent a car

04:04.778 --> 04:06.380
that runs on water.

04:06.414 --> 04:07.815
MAX: Congratulations.
FRANKIE: Thank you.

04:07.848 --> 04:10.017
Max, you have a shot.

04:10.050 --> 04:11.419
When you turn 18,
it won't make a difference.

04:11.452 --> 04:12.853
I'll get ordained
and marry you.

04:12.886 --> 04:14.388
MAX:
You would do that?

04:14.422 --> 04:15.589
FRANKIE: Yes, but I'll get
ordained as a Satanist,

04:15.623 --> 04:17.458
and you have to give
me your firstborn

04:17.491 --> 04:19.259
so I can drink its blood.

04:19.293 --> 04:20.361
MAX:
Yeah, okay, I'd do that.

04:20.394 --> 04:22.129
For Mr. Thompson, yeah.

04:22.162 --> 04:23.364
FRANKIE:
So it's settled.

04:23.397 --> 04:24.798
MAX:
Yes, it is.

04:24.832 --> 04:26.467
Does it have to be
my firstborn?

04:26.500 --> 04:28.101
FRANKIE: Yes.
MAX: Can I give you my husband?

04:28.135 --> 04:29.403
FRANKIE:
No.

04:29.437 --> 04:30.771
MAX:
All right, whatever.

04:30.804 --> 04:31.939
Classy.

04:31.972 --> 04:33.574
Why would you
post that, though?

04:33.607 --> 04:36.377
(Frankie and Max laughing)

04:36.410 --> 04:39.112
Okay, so when you hit
the vape too hard.

04:39.146 --> 04:42.215
* Is now, is now.

04:42.249 --> 04:44.217
(singers vocalizing)

04:44.251 --> 04:49.623
* Mother, you had me

04:49.657 --> 04:54.328
* But I never had you

04:54.362 --> 04:56.196
*

04:58.466 --> 05:02.336
* I wanted you

05:04.037 --> 05:08.976
* You didn't want me.

05:09.009 --> 05:11.178
*

05:11.211 --> 05:13.681
MAN:
Stop! Let's go this way.

05:13.714 --> 05:15.315
MAN 2:
That's what you said before!

05:15.349 --> 05:16.484
I'm not going!

05:16.517 --> 05:18.285
(high-pitched):
Don't be stupid.

05:18.318 --> 05:19.387
At least not now!

05:19.420 --> 05:21.455
You'd better be right!

05:21.489 --> 05:22.623
(sobbing):
Oh, come on.

05:22.656 --> 05:23.957
This way!

05:23.991 --> 05:26.259
(yells)
For crying in Pete's face,

05:26.293 --> 05:27.628
just come on!

05:27.661 --> 05:31.765
(groans loudly)

05:31.799 --> 05:34.001
(both screaming)

05:34.034 --> 05:38.238
(groans):
Get out of my cave!

05:38.271 --> 05:39.640
I told you!

05:39.673 --> 05:42.643
(groans loudly)

05:43.644 --> 05:44.812
Hmm?

05:44.845 --> 05:46.279
Lightning in a bottle.
Hitler.

05:46.313 --> 05:48.248
(laughs)
If it ain't broke, don't--

05:48.281 --> 05:49.883
If it ain't broke
don't fix it, right?
He's only got one ball!

05:50.951 --> 05:52.786
Are we good?
(whoops)

05:52.820 --> 05:53.987
(page turns)

05:54.021 --> 05:56.089
This is torture.

05:56.123 --> 05:58.626
Max, you have to drive.

05:58.659 --> 06:00.661
You need a license,
you have to wait in line.

06:00.694 --> 06:02.295
Yeah, I have to drive?

06:02.329 --> 06:05.499
My friends and I
couldn't wait to do this

06:05.533 --> 06:07.367
the second we turned 15.
Blah, blah.

06:07.401 --> 06:08.702
And the phones,
they were really big

06:08.736 --> 06:10.504
and they stayed
in your house.

06:10.538 --> 06:12.440
Oh, my God.

06:12.473 --> 06:16.209
We both suck.

06:16.243 --> 06:17.645
Can't we just go
to Dollar Bag

06:17.678 --> 06:18.912
and get Jolly Ranchers?

06:18.946 --> 06:20.213
Forward, Max.

06:20.247 --> 06:22.382
Your life needs to move forward.

06:22.416 --> 06:25.486
(phone vibrates)

06:25.519 --> 06:27.455
Hi. Hi.

06:27.488 --> 06:28.689
ROBIN:
Hi.

06:28.722 --> 06:30.057
Is it okay that I'm calling?

06:30.090 --> 06:33.260
Well, I did give you my number.
(laughs)

06:33.293 --> 06:34.495
How are you?

06:34.528 --> 06:35.663
I'm good.

06:35.696 --> 06:36.997
Yeah, I'm good.

06:37.030 --> 06:41.201
So, this is, uh...

06:41.234 --> 06:43.671
I'm gonna take a big swing
right now.

06:43.704 --> 06:45.405
Uh, go for it.

06:45.439 --> 06:47.074
Yeah?

06:47.107 --> 06:48.676
Yeah. Hi. What?

06:48.709 --> 06:50.277
I was planning on going

06:50.310 --> 06:52.112
up to El Cevitas this weekend.

06:52.145 --> 06:53.914
Mia has an overnight
with her school

06:53.947 --> 06:56.083
so I'm going away.

06:56.116 --> 06:57.417
So...

06:57.451 --> 06:59.319
I'm going to invite you
to come with me,

06:59.352 --> 07:00.988
to spend the weekend with me
in El Cevitas,

07:01.021 --> 07:03.691
and we can taste some wine

07:03.724 --> 07:05.025
or look at some art,

07:05.058 --> 07:08.228
uh, have some great food,

07:08.261 --> 07:10.864
and... yeah.

07:10.898 --> 07:13.534
Yeah, big, big weekend.

07:13.567 --> 07:16.169
Asking you to spend
the weekend, so...

07:16.203 --> 07:17.505
big swing.

07:17.538 --> 07:19.039
Yeah.

07:19.072 --> 07:21.809
That is a big swing there,
chief.

07:21.842 --> 07:24.111
You know what, I like you.

07:24.144 --> 07:28.048
I know it's-it's early
for me to be asking you

07:28.081 --> 07:32.019
to go away with me,
but I'm doing it

07:32.052 --> 07:34.788
because I like you that much.

07:34.822 --> 07:37.525
Uh, I just feel like we got off

07:37.558 --> 07:41.261
on such an unconventional foot
here and...

07:41.294 --> 07:44.532
I already had this trip planned

07:44.565 --> 07:48.335
and I don't want to wait until
next weekend to see you again,

07:48.368 --> 07:51.539
uh, because I... (sighs)

07:51.572 --> 07:53.273
I'm gonna stop there.

07:53.306 --> 07:56.744
Just, if you want to come,
please do.

07:56.777 --> 07:58.078
You're invited.

07:58.111 --> 07:59.279
And also...

07:59.312 --> 08:01.081
(line beeps)
Wait, what?

08:01.114 --> 08:02.583
Did you hear what I said?

08:02.616 --> 08:04.017
(line beeps)
Hold on.

08:19.733 --> 08:22.135
Um, I need to think about it.

08:22.169 --> 08:23.403
Is that okay?

08:23.436 --> 08:25.238
Yeah. More than okay.

08:25.272 --> 08:26.674
Really?
Yes.

08:26.707 --> 08:29.376
I'd be weirded out
if you said yes right away.

08:29.409 --> 08:31.478
(laughs) What?

08:31.511 --> 08:33.981
No, I mean, you know,
please go ahead.

08:34.014 --> 08:36.316
Talk to your girlfriends
about it.
Ew.

08:36.349 --> 08:38.185
Or don't.

08:38.218 --> 08:40.420
However you want to...
Okay. I'll...

08:40.453 --> 08:42.623
I'll call you later, okay?

08:42.656 --> 08:44.558
Yes. Yes, okay.

08:46.226 --> 08:47.695
Okay.

08:47.728 --> 08:48.929
Hey.

08:48.962 --> 08:50.798
Yeah?

08:50.831 --> 08:52.332
That was nice.

08:52.365 --> 08:54.534
Thank you for asking.

08:54.568 --> 08:56.469
I like it...

08:56.503 --> 08:58.639
how you asked.

08:58.672 --> 08:59.707
Okay.

08:59.740 --> 09:02.009
Bye.

09:04.211 --> 09:06.213
Ooh.

09:06.246 --> 09:09.382
Good move, buddy.

09:09.416 --> 09:13.220
Good move. Good move.

09:15.322 --> 09:17.691
Ooh.

09:24.698 --> 09:27.735
Oh, my God, we're not
going back in there.

09:27.768 --> 09:29.436
(groans)

09:32.105 --> 09:33.674
JOY:
We're estranged now.

09:33.707 --> 09:35.876
One year, she made me
flaming cherries jubilee.

09:35.909 --> 09:37.510
It was really good.

09:37.544 --> 09:39.512
I can't even remember
what we fought about.

09:39.546 --> 09:41.248
I don't know.

09:41.281 --> 09:45.452
I just feel like I still have
a lot of stuff left to do.

09:45.485 --> 09:47.220
I don't know. I can't
believe it's my birthday.

09:47.254 --> 09:49.657
It was really sweet
of you guys to take me out.

09:49.690 --> 09:51.825
I can't believe
I'm old enough to drink.

09:51.859 --> 09:54.394
(laughs)

09:54.427 --> 09:55.863
What's going on with you?

09:55.896 --> 09:58.766
Huh? Nothing.

09:58.799 --> 10:01.201
Nothing.

10:01.234 --> 10:03.370
Hi. Happy birthday.

10:03.403 --> 10:05.205
Yay, birthday!
Thank you.

10:05.238 --> 10:07.240
JOY: This is such
a great birthday. Yay!
TRESSA: We love you.

10:07.274 --> 10:08.275
Thank you.

10:08.308 --> 10:09.576
L'chaim.
Thank you.

10:09.609 --> 10:10.911
TRESSA:
Mazel.

10:10.944 --> 10:13.380
Oh.
Mmm.

10:13.413 --> 10:15.215
I'm tipsy.
(laughs)

10:15.248 --> 10:16.950
(laughing):
Aw.

10:16.984 --> 10:18.251
Bye, honey, love you.

10:18.285 --> 10:19.653
Bye. I love you, too.

10:24.658 --> 10:27.527
Hi. Hi.

10:27.560 --> 10:30.864
Uh, I would, uh...

10:30.898 --> 10:33.133
I would like to join you
this weekend.

10:33.166 --> 10:35.468
Um, very much so.

10:35.502 --> 10:39.406
So, uh, just wanted
to say that, okay?

10:39.439 --> 10:42.575
I'm, uh, hanging up now.

10:42.609 --> 10:43.844
Bye.

10:45.913 --> 10:47.580
Where are you going?

10:47.614 --> 10:49.249
I'm packing.

10:49.282 --> 10:50.483
Mom, where are you going?

10:50.517 --> 10:52.119
Bitch, I'm going to the moon.

10:52.152 --> 10:53.954
My God, Mom,
that's so offensive.

10:53.987 --> 10:56.089
I'm so fat.

10:56.123 --> 10:57.124
Can't believe
I have a boyfriend.

10:57.157 --> 10:58.258
Who's staying with us?

10:58.291 --> 10:59.292
Stay with us what?

10:59.326 --> 11:01.294
Susie.
Mom, no way.

11:01.328 --> 11:02.629
Wait, where are you going?

11:02.662 --> 11:04.097
She's going
to the moon, bitch.

11:04.131 --> 11:05.398
Shut up, Frankie.

11:05.432 --> 11:06.734
Mom, Mom, we don't need Susie.

11:06.767 --> 11:08.268
I can watch everyone.

11:08.301 --> 11:10.170
No. Mom, don't leave us
with Susie. She sucks.

11:10.203 --> 11:12.172
And don't leave us with Max.
She's so much worse.

11:12.205 --> 11:14.174
SAM:
Fine. Then no one's coming.

11:14.207 --> 11:15.809
I don't care.

11:15.843 --> 11:17.610
Can I have a couple friends
over? Not a party.

11:17.644 --> 11:18.846
I don't care.

11:18.879 --> 11:20.180
Run away while I'm gone.

11:20.213 --> 11:22.282
I don't care about any of it.

11:22.315 --> 11:24.417
There's nothing in this house
that's worth anything to me,

11:24.451 --> 11:25.953
except the art.

11:25.986 --> 11:27.955
Don't mess with my paintings.
Good-bye.

11:27.988 --> 11:29.356
MAX: Mom, I don't get
what your problem is.

11:29.389 --> 11:30.623
You're my problem.

11:30.657 --> 11:32.559
You're insane.

11:32.592 --> 11:34.161
Why'd you say "I'm going
to the moon, bitch"?

11:34.194 --> 11:35.863
FRANKIE: I don't know.
She said it to me.

11:35.896 --> 11:37.630
MAX: Mom, you're not
serious, are you?

11:37.664 --> 11:39.199
FRANKIE: Mom, you still have
to take me to Chloe's house

11:39.232 --> 11:41.168
on Saturday.
What are you doing at Chloe's?

11:41.201 --> 11:43.536
I just want to know.
Well, what are you gonna
do with your friends?

11:43.570 --> 11:45.172
Mom, this is
child abandonment.

11:45.205 --> 11:46.706
We're like orphans now.

11:46.740 --> 11:48.375
I don't care.

11:48.408 --> 11:50.043
You guys can move out

11:50.077 --> 11:51.812
and get an apartment together
when I'm gone.

11:51.845 --> 11:53.380
Seriously.

11:53.413 --> 11:55.415
I'll cosign the lease right now
to make that happen.

11:55.448 --> 11:57.450
MAX: Oh, my God,
Mom, it is so mean

11:57.484 --> 11:58.786
that you're saying
that to me, Mom.

11:58.819 --> 12:00.587
Wait, Mom.
Mom, did you mean it?

12:00.620 --> 12:01.922
I want to get an apartment.

12:01.955 --> 12:04.391
Mom!

12:04.424 --> 12:06.794
Mom!

12:11.765 --> 12:13.100
(tires screech)

12:16.069 --> 12:18.171
Yoo-hoo!

12:18.205 --> 12:20.607
(stammers)

12:31.418 --> 12:35.022
So, what do you do when you
have a minute to yourself?

12:35.055 --> 12:36.924
Oh.

12:36.957 --> 12:38.691
I drink alcohol
and I sleep.

12:38.725 --> 12:40.393
(laughs)

12:40.427 --> 12:43.230
If I have two minutes, I watch
murder shows on cable.

12:43.263 --> 12:47.167
Oh. Murder like Law & Order
or murder like real murder?

12:47.200 --> 12:49.636
Oh, no, only ever real murder.

12:49.669 --> 12:52.940
I could jack off to real people
being murdered for hours.

12:52.973 --> 12:55.075
Why do you like
murder so much?

12:55.108 --> 12:56.709
I don't know.

12:56.743 --> 12:59.479
I, uh, fantasize
about being murdered.

12:59.512 --> 13:00.747
You do?

13:00.780 --> 13:02.782
Yeah.

13:02.816 --> 13:05.853
I mean, it feels like
I'm being murdered every day

13:05.886 --> 13:08.655
in a vague way that no one
could prosecute anyone for,

13:08.688 --> 13:10.858
so when I see these stories

13:10.891 --> 13:13.226
about the lady
who gets her head chopped off,

13:13.260 --> 13:15.362
and they find hairs
on the guy's knife

13:15.395 --> 13:16.796
and he gets
put away for life,

13:16.830 --> 13:19.299
that's, like,
very satisfying, you know?

13:19.332 --> 13:21.801
Nope.

13:21.835 --> 13:23.170
No?
You don't get it.

13:23.203 --> 13:24.637
(laughing):
No, I get it. I do.

13:24.671 --> 13:26.940
(laughing):
You... come on.
I do. Sorry.

13:26.974 --> 13:28.641
(both laughing)

13:28.675 --> 13:30.477
Oh.

13:30.510 --> 13:34.781
Yeah, the year that, uh, Mia's
mom took off was really bad.

13:34.814 --> 13:37.750
Yeah.
Yeah, really, really bad.

13:37.784 --> 13:41.121
I had a cool job,
but the money wasn't huge,

13:41.154 --> 13:43.356
so I had to quit it
so I could concentrate more

13:43.390 --> 13:46.159
on earning and-and raising her.

